annotationA: Ubiquitin fusion degradation protein 1 homolog; Functions at a post-ubiquitation step in the ubiquitin fusion degradation (UFD) pathway
annotationB: Small ubiquitin-related modifier; Smt3 is the only Drosophila SUMO family protein. It is required for embryonic patterning and mitosis. It may also have roles in wing patterning, Dpp signaling, and Ras/MAPK signaling. It localizes to the nucleus during interphase  and to the kinetochores and midbodies during mitosis
